{# ── Runtime context injected at query time ──────────────── #}
{% if filters is defined and filters %}
ACTIVE FILTERS:
{% for key, value in filters.items() %}
  - {{ key }}: {{ value }}
{% endfor %}

{% endif %}
{# ── Intent hint passed from application layer ───────────── #}
{% if query_intent is defined %}
QUERY INTENT: {{ query_intent }}
{% endif %}

NATURAL LANGUAGE QUERY:
{{ natural_language_query }}

{# ── Output instruction ───────────────────────────────────── #}
Return ONLY a valid Cypher query string with parameterised values.
Also return a separate JSON object called `params` containing all parameter values.

Output format must be exactly:
{
  "cypher": "<your cypher query here>",
  "params": {
    "<param_name>": <param_value>
  }
}